# Keeps the Docker build context (repo root — see packages/control-plane-bot/Dockerfile) to
# just what a scoped pnpm install/build actually needs. Without this, `COPY . .` would ship a
# host-platform node_modules (breaks a Linux image build on Windows/macOS dev machines) and
# every package's dist/coverage output straight into the build context.
node_modules
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/*.tsbuildinfo
coverage
**/coverage
.git
.claude
tasks
scratch
*.local
*.log
# Deploy secrets must never enter the build context: the build stage does `COPY . .`, so
# without this an operator's real deploy/.env (Discord bot token) would be baked into a build
# image layer even though the runtime stage never copies it. Secrets reach the container at
# run time via docker-compose env_file/environment, never through the image.
*.env
**/.env
deploy/.env
